    {
      "reviewerId": null,
      "reviewerUrl": null,
      "name": null,
      "reviewerNumberOfReviews": 9,
      "isLocalGuide": false,
      "reviewerPhotoUrl": null,
      "text": "My aunt has been battling Parkinson's disease for about 10 years, and her caregiver needed to return to Indonesia to see her daughter, prompting us to transition my aunt to a nursing home. After searching through many elderly care centers in jb area, some felt overly commercialized.\n\nHowever, this family care center provided a homelike environment and clean! The staff who had medical knowledge, provided exceptional care. Witnessing my aunt laughter, a rare occurrence after years of struggle with Parkinson’s disease, was truly heartwarming and indicative of her comfort in this family care center.\n\nAdditionally, her bed sores healed quickly under their attentive care. I highly recommend this family care center! ❤️ Thank you so much Ms Ho and the team 🥰👍🏻👍🏻👍🏻",
      "textTranslated": null,
      "publishAt": "2 years ago",
      "publishedAtDate": "2024-05-07T08:32:00.072Z",
      "likesCount": 1,
      "reviewId": "ChZDSUhNMG9nS0VJQ0FnSURqMDlIWFBBEAE",
